The General Agreement on Tariffs andTrade (GATT) will begin a probe on May 7-8 on the legality ofJapanese import restrictions on 12 farm products, AgricultureMinistry officials said.    The investigation, which will take place in Geneva, followsa U.S. Complaint last year that the restrictions violated GATTrules prohibiting import quotas.    The products involved include fruit juice, peanuts andtomato juice. Reuter&#3;